abstract: The bride is a law clerk and the groom is an associate at a law firm.
snippet: The bride is a law clerk and the groom is an associate at a law firm.
lead_paragraph: Emily Gordon Hankin, a daughter of Ann D. Hankin and Michael D. Hankin of Butler, Md., was married Saturday to James Joseph Petrila, a son of Judith E. Stein and James P. Petrila of Washington. The Rev. Tracy A. Bruce performed the ceremony at St. John’s Episcopal Church in Glyndon, Md.

lead_paragraph: 8 P.M. (HBO) DAWN OF THE PLANET OF THE APES (2014) A decade has passed on screen since “Rise of the Planet of the Apes,” and millions of people have fallen prey to a lethal virus, leaving survivors to cobble together a society in the ruins of San Francisco, where Dreyfus (Gary Oldman), the former police chief, is in charge. But across the Golden Gate Bridge in Marin County, the upright-walking chimpanzee Caesar (Andy Serkis) and his team have built their own civilization, complete with distinctive wooden architecture, domesticated horses, a sophisticated sign language and an education system overseen by the orangutan Maurice (Karin Konoval). But when the humans ask to encroach on their territory to build a hydroelectric station, the alarms are sounded — and schisms formed. “It’s a satisfying movie and an example — a dispiritingly rare one these days — of what mainstream Hollywood filmmaking can still achieve,” A. O. Scott wrote in The New York Times about Matt Reeves’s Oscar nominee for best achievement in visual effects. “That we have progressed from ‘Rise’ only as far as ‘Dawn’ suggests many future sequels, which may, in this case, be a source of hope as well as dread, provided that civilization doesn’t collapse in the meantime.”

headline_main: Things to Do on Long Island, May 24 to 30, 2015

abstract: Some Twitter users lashed out in sometimes profanity-laced replies that exhort the president, who is using @POTUS, to kill himself and worse.
snippet: Some Twitter users lashed out in sometimes profanity-laced replies that exhort the president, who is using @POTUS, to kill himself and worse.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Obama sent his inaugural Twitter post from the Oval Office on Monday, the White House heralded the event with fanfare, posting a photograph of him perched on his desk tapping out his message on an iPhone.

abstract: Survivors described scenes of sudden horror, as train cars tumbled off the tracks and passengers, tossed like dolls, looked for a way out.
snippet: Survivors described scenes of sudden horror, as train cars tumbled off the tracks and passengers, tossed like dolls, looked for a way out.
lead_paragraph: Jeremy Wladis was well settled into an evening train home from Washington on Tuesday, a commute he does at least once a week, his tablet, his smartphone, a notebook and pen arrayed in front of him to work.

abstract: Earlier governments at least pretended to adhere to universal democratic norms. The prime minister’s new coalition is an outright denial of them.
snippet: Earlier governments at least pretended to adhere to universal democratic norms. The prime minister’s new coalition is an outright denial of them.
lead_paragraph: In Israel, we are used to hearing that everything is more “complex” than one might think. Situations are typically described as variegated, imprecise or intangible and they seem almost intentionally so. Implicitness — about politics, religion, military actions, and human rights — rules. But I would argue that that situation has changed. In the past year in Israel, things have become clear and precise. Things have become explicit.

abstract: The two actors, both nominated for Tony Awards, discuss the physical nature of their roles in “Hand to God” and “The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time.”
snippet: The two actors, both nominated for Tony Awards, discuss the physical nature of their roles in “Hand to God” and “The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-Time.”
lead_paragraph: Steven Boyer has a broken finger. Alex Sharp has a hairline fracture in his elbow. Their bodies are bruised; their voices strained. And every day, they come back for more.
